node.text: Take a ride at 139 KMH down the St. Moritz luge track. The only Olympic style track in the world hand built out of snow and ice every single year. The top part is slow but I promise it picks up really fast after ;) Enjoy!

node.text:
St. Moritz, Switzerland. The only hand cut track in the world, and I was fortunate enough to watch the track crew build it by hand. It's amazing that in just 3 weeks the track crew can build over 2000 meters of track out of snow and ice! 
This will be the track used for the @lausanne2020 Winter Youth Olympics.
Thank you @Olympicchannel for making this possible. 
@YouthOlympics @Athlete365 @Olympics @fil_Luge

node.title: Watch one of the fastest tracks in the world St. Moritz being built by hand

142 miles of dirt roads, washes and obstacles all tackled in 2 days. What an epic adventure through some of the most unique landscapes in the world. I promise Utah doesn’t pay me to say that! I’m just lucky enough to have traveled to many parts of this Earth and know first hand how special this place is. Thanks @toyotausa and @teamtoyota for helping me explore one of the most remote places in the state! Thanks Deborah for exploring and getting lost with me in #theswell! 
#letsgoplaces #kaizen #beautahful #toyota #teamtoyota

node.text:
The Olympics have taught me that no matter what dream, ambition or aspiration you may have, there is a chance that through hard work, perseverance and a never-give-up attitude that it can come true. From the moment that I found my sport it took over two decades and a lot of set backs to finally realize my childhood dream. 
But that is why we dream! That is why we push ourselves! We sometimes believe in our mission and goals when no one else does. Sometimes it works out, most of the time it doesn't. But I would rather give it everything than sitting around and wondering what could have happened if I tried just a little harder or gave a little bit more?
It's the struggle that defines us. The lessons and experiences learned along the way shape who we are. No matter what your goals and dreams are. Go for them! That is what Olympic day is all about!
#teamusa #olympics #olympicday #luge #dreams #dreamsdocometrue #goals #roadtobeijing #roadtobeijing2022

node.text:
I'm not really sure if I have had enough time to fully understand what being a father is all about, but I do know that life has definitely changed. It has been an amazing experience overall but I don't think that I was prepared for the challenges I would face in terms of managing my previous self Identity, managing time and most importantly managing my relationships. 
My priorities have definitely shifted and juggling everything feels very overwhelming, especially when you throw feeding, changing diapers and cleaning everything up on what’s seems like an every two hour schedule. But by far the hardest part of this is keeping up all of your normal relationships and most importantly the one with your spouse. 
There is no baby manual (you will feel this the first time you leave a hospital with a newborn and drive away with that sinking "holy shit is this real" feeling) and disagreements are a big part of parenting. The hardest part of parenting so far has been communicating how I am feeling, what I am thinking and working through those differences. It was hard but we have come a long way in these first two months. I also forget to make time for Mara because it is surprisingly easy to use every minute of the day and next thing you know it's time for bed. Overall, this has been a huge adjustment for me and there is so much that I have needed to learn in order to be the best dad for my family. 
But here is the real talk, it's ok. This shit is hard. And we are all going to mess it up at times. But as long as I know what's hard (talking, making time for others, whats best for Nico) I can work towards being the best dad and husband. 
Being a dad has definitely taken me away from some parts in my life, but I love what it has given me in return. There is so much to learn and grow and I can’t wait to have this little guy by my side the whole way!
